Class Fact

  • java.lang.Object
    • tags.Tag
      • tags.Predicate
        • tags.Fact
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Tag>

    public class Fact
extends Predicate
    Represents a fact in the Expert System. Facts are calculus predicates that represent something that is seen as true.

    Facts are composed of a predicate name and a set of arguments: P(ARG1, ARG2, ...)

    • Constructor Detail

      • Fact

        public Fact(java.lang.String value,
            double confidenceValue)
        Constructs a Fact object from a string

        NB: There should be no space characters between the arguments in a string i.e. "P(ARG1,ARG2,ARG3...)". Arguments are delimited by commas within parenthesis.

        Parameters:
        value - String input
        confidenceValue - double in range [0,1] i.e. 0.n representing n0% confidence
